article.linkText: Flowers scores 25 to lead St. Bonaventure over Binghamton 90-64
article.story: OLEAN, N.Y. -- — Moses Flowers' 25 points helped Saint Bonaventure defeat Binghamton 90-64 on Friday night. Flowers shot 8 for 13 (5 for 8 from 3-point range) and 4 of 4 from the free throw line for the Bonnies (8-3). Mika Adams-Woods scored 14 points while going 5 of 9 from the floor, including 1 for 3 from 3-point range, and 3 for 4 from the line, and added six assists. Charles Pride was 5 of 7 shooting (3 for 5 from 3-point range) to finish with 13 points. The Bearcats (7-5) were led by Tymu Chenery, who posted 14 points. Dan Petcash added 10 points. Symir Torrence also recorded nine points, six rebounds and nine assists. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
